task.summary: transform view has landed with implicit evaluation when used on a LHS of an asignment to an std::vector (other containers currently not supported)
scalar renamed to repeat to make it consistent with rangesV3

removed old code
first version of async works. it uses the transform algorithm with an identity function to materialize a view into an gvector
async supports now the function style call as well as the pipelining syntax
async now takes all kind of input stuff
restructured the library. the reduce algorithm has landed!
reduction is now (using msp) slightly faster than thrust
reduction is now (using msp) slightly faster than thrust for all input sizes until aprox. 2^27
made reduction safe for input sizes < 128
added for_each algorithm and ref wrapper for gvector
reduction now uses 1024 threads for input sizes >= 2^24. now gstorm is always faster than thrust
